<p>I need to get index of macro repetition element to write next code:  </p>  <pre><code>struct A {     data: [i32; 3] }  macro_rules! tst {     ( $( $n:ident ),* ) =&gt; {         impl A {             $(                 fn $n(self) -&gt; i32 {                     self.data[?] // here I need the index                 }             ),*         }     } } </code></pre>  <p>I know one way to do it: just tell user to write index by hands: </p>  <pre><code>( $( $i:ident =&gt; $n:ident ),* ) </code></pre>  <p>But is there a more elegant way which does not require user's action?</p>